    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.body.text }}",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "type": "SystemMessagePromptTemplate",
              "message": "You are an expert invoice data extraction parser operating in a strict automated pipeline.\nYour task is to extract structured financial information from invoice text or OCR output.\nYou must return ONLY a valid JSON object. Do not include markdown formatting, explanations, or any other text.\n\nRequired JSON structure:\n{\n  \"supplier\": \"string or null\",\n  \"vat_id\": \"string or null\",\n  \"iban\": \"string or null\",\n  \"var_symbol\": \"string or null\",\n  \"net_amount\": \"number or null\",\n  \"vat_amount\": \"number or null\",\n  \"total_amount\": \"number or null\",\n  \"due_date\": \"string (ISO 8601 date) or null\",\n  \"validation_status\": \"ok|missing_fields|suspicious or null\"\n}\n\nExtraction rules:\n1. If a value is not explicitly mentioned, set it to null.\n2. vat_id: extract Czech IČO or DIČ (format CZ + 8-10 digits).\n3. iban: extract full IBAN if present, otherwise null.\n4. All amounts: output as numbers without currency symbols.\n5. due_date: always ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-DD).\n6. validation_status: set to \"suspicious\" if total_amount differs from net_amount + vat_amount by more than 1 CZK."
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
      "id": "wf001a-llm",
      "name": "LLM Extract",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
      "position": [300, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "// WF-001 Validation Gate — universal\n// Change requiredFields per variant\n\nconst rawOutput = $input.item.json.text ?? $input.item.json.output;\nlet extractedData;\nlet isValid = true;\nlet errorMessages = [];\n\ntry {\n  extractedData = typeof rawOutput === 'string'\n    ? JSON.parse(rawOutput)\n    : rawOutput;\n} catch (error) {\n  return [{\n    json: {\n      status: \"error\",\n      errors: [\"Failed to parse LLM output as JSON\"],\n      rawData: rawOutput\n    }\n  }];\n}\n\nconst requiredFields = ['supplier', 'net_amount', 'total_amount', 'due_date'];\n\nfor (const field of requiredFields) {\n  if (\n    !extractedData.hasOwnProperty(field) ||\n    extractedData[field] === null ||\n    extractedData[field] === \"\"\n  ) {\n    isValid = false;\n    errorMessages.push(`Missing critical field: ${field}`);\n  }\n}\n\nif (isValid) {\n  return [{ json: { status: \"success\", data: extractedData } }];\n} else {\n  return [{ json: { status: \"error\", errors: errorMessages, partialData: extractedData } }];\n}"
      },
      "id": "wf001a-validation",
      "name": "Validation Gate",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [600, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "rules",
        "rules": {
          "values": [
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": true,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "strict",
                  "version": 2
                },
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "id": "wf001a-cond-success",
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.status }}",
                    "rightValue": "success",
                    "operator": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "operation": "equals"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "combinator": "and"
              },
              "renameOutput": true,
              "outputKey": "success"
            },
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": true,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "strict",
                  "version": 2
                },
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "id": "wf001a-cond-error",
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.status }}",
                    "rightValue": "error",
